Network Analysis

In this notebook, we provide the code for the network analysis appendix.

library("igraph")
library("sna")
library("RColorBrewer")
library("netnew")

First, we define the functions used to compute the statistics and plot the graphs:

netstats = function(fields = "all"){
  rawdata = read.csv("tselinks_ext.csv")
  colnames(rawdata) <- c("id","name","field","level","mf","f1","f2","f3","f4","f5","f6","f7","f8","f9","f10","f11","f12")
  rawdata <- subset(rawdata, field != "none")
  
  if (fields=="admin"){
    rawdata <- subset(rawdata, field == fields)
  }
  
  if ((fields!="admin")&(fields!="all")){
    rawdata <- subset(rawdata, field == fields)
  }
  
  # Adj Matrix:
  
  unique_names <- unique(c(rawdata$name))
  
  # Create an empty adjacency matrix
  adj_matrix <- matrix(0, nrow = length(unique_names), ncol = length(unique_names))
  
  # Iterate over each row in rawdata
  for (i in 1:nrow(rawdata)) {
    person <- rawdata$name[i]
    person <- which(unique_names == person)
    
    # Iterate over each friend column and update adjacency matrix
    for (j in 1:12) {
      friend <- rawdata[[paste0("f", j)]][i]
      friend <- which(unique_names == friend)
      
      if (length(friend)!=0){
        if (!is.na(friend)){
          adj_matrix[person, friend] <- 1
        }
      }
    }
  }
  
  cat("GROUP:", fields, "\n")
  cat("--- mean degree:", mean(rowMeans(adj_matrix)/dim(adj_matrix)[1]),"\n")
  cat("--- centralisat:",   sd(rowMeans(adj_matrix)/dim(adj_matrix)[1]),"\n")
  cat("--- bicomponent:",   sum(bicomponent.dist(adj_matrix)$csize),"\n")
  cat("--- laplacian 1:",   eigen_lap(adj_matrix),"\n")
  cat("--- laplacian 2:",   eigen_lap(adj_matrix, n=2),"\n")
  cat("--- assortativi:",   assortativity(adj_matrix),"\n")
  cat("--- transitivit:",   transitivity(graph_from_adjacency_matrix(adj_matrix)),"\n")
  
  graphigraph = igraph::graph_from_adjacency_matrix(adj_matrix,mode="directed")

  if ((fields!="admin")&(fields!="all")){
    # create a color map
    
    rawdata["color"] = numeric()
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="phd"] = '#BEBADA'
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="ap"] = '#8DD3C7'
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="full"] = '#FFFFB3'
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="post"] = '#FB8072'
      
    V(graphigraph)$color <- rawdata$color
    
    plot(graphigraph, main=fields)
    legend("topleft", legend=c("phd","ap","full","post"), pch=16, col=c('#BEBADA','#8DD3C7','#FFFFB3','#FB8072'))
  }
  if (fields=="all"){
    
    rawdata["color"] = numeric()
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="phd"] = '#BEBADA'
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="ap"] = '#8DD3C7'
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="full"] = '#FFFFB3'
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="post"] = '#FB8072'
    rawdata["color"][rawdata["level"]=="admin"] = '#FFB999'
      
    V(graphigraph)$color <- rawdata$color
    l=layout_nicely(graphigraph, dim=3)
    
    plot(graphigraph, main=fields, layout=l)
    legend("topleft", legend=c("phd","ap","full","post","admin"), pch=16, col=c('#BEBADA','#8DD3C7','#FFFFB3','#FB8072','#FFB999'))
  }
  if (fields=="admin"){
    plot(graphigraph,main="admin")
  }
}
